{{wikipediapar|Selling coal to Newcastle}}
==English==
===Etymology===
[[w:Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle upon Tyne]] (in [[Britain]]) was a major [[coal]] exporting city, so sending coal there would be pointless.
===Phrase===
'''[[coal]]s to [[Newcastle]]'''
# A pointless [[venture]], in the sense of sending something to a place where it's made, or where they already have an [[abundance]].
#: 1935: ''No more coals to Newcastle, no more Hoares to Paris'' &mdash; attributed to [[w:George V of the United Kingdom|King George V of the United Kingdom]], but possibly a joke doing the rounds at the time (see [[q:George V of the United Kingdom|wikiquote]])

